    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a revised version with a more personal touch:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and the enthusiasm you brought to the final interview. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture requirements.\n\nI want to emphasize that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your qualifications and potential. Your passion for coding and problem-solving is evident, and we appreciate the time and effort you invested in our interview process. We were particularly struck by your ability to think creatively and outside the box, qualities that are essential for success in our fast-paced tech environment.\n\nAlthough we didn't find the right fit for this role, I want to assure you that we're keeping your name in mind for future opportunities that may align with your skills and interests. We recognize that our needs can change, and we'd love to have the chance to work with someone as talented as you in the future. If our requirements shift, we'd definitely consider reaching out to you again.\n\nIf you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out. We",
